de.oaam.model.oaam.hardware

Interface Connection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, ResourceProviderInstanceA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectionImpl

    public interface Connection
extends ResourceProviderInstanceA, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA, ModeDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Connection'. A connection is a communication line between two devices. It can be a single wire, a bus or even wireless depending on the connection type.

    The following features are supported:

    • Type
    • Starting Points
    • End Points
    • Masters
    See Also:
    HardwarePackage.getConnection()

        ConnectionType getType()
        Returns the value of the 'Type' reference. A reference to the type of the connection. The type specifies the properties, like topology and provided resources.

      • getStartingPoints

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Io> getStartingPoints()
        Returns the value of the 'Starting Points' reference list. The list contents are of type Io. All starting points of the connection. The differentiation between starting and endpoints is only relevant for unidirectional connections. In case of a bidirectional connection starts and ends are equal.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Starting Points' reference list.
        See Also:
        HardwarePackage.getConnection_StartingPoints()

      • getEndPoints

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Io> getEndPoints()
        Returns the value of the 'End Points' reference list. The list contents are of type Io. All endpoints of the connection. The differentiation between starting and endpoints is only relevant for unidirectional connections. In case of a bidirectional connection starts and ends are equal.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'End Points' reference list.
        See Also:
        HardwarePackage.getConnection_EndPoints()

      • getMasters

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Io> getMasters()
        Returns the value of the 'Masters' reference list. The list contents are of type Io. All masters of the connection. The IO or IOs that controll the buss. This should only be set if this is a master controlled bus system. See the requiresMaster attribute in the connection type.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Masters' reference list.
        See Also:
        HardwarePackage.getConnection_Masters()
